                            <comment id="97806" author="isaac" created="Wed, 29 Oct 2014 06:04:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another one:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/197aed5c-592e-11e4-8f95-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/197aed5c-592e-11e4-8f95-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appeared to be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3455&quot; title=&quot;Test failure replay-single, test_20b: after 23936 &amp;gt; before 9600&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3455&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3455&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The test_6 tried to get before=$(kbytesfree) after file removal and some wait:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;    rm -f $f
    sync &amp;amp;&amp;amp; sleep 5 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; sync  # wait for delete thread

    # wait till space is returned, following
    # (( $before &amp;gt; $after_dd)) test counting on that
    wait_mds_ost_sync || return 4
    wait_destroy_complete || return 5

    local before=$(kbytesfree)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d doubt the wait can work reliably with ZFS - sometimes frees can be delayed for a few transaction groups&apos; time. It seemed inherently unreliable to free and wait and get free space for ZFS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
